1) External Css 
- create css file and import 

Example 1) 
import React from 'react'
import "./person.css";

const Person1 = () => {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>This is test</h1>
      <p className='para'>This is para</p>
    </div>
  )
}

export default Person1; 



2) Inline Css 

Example 2) 
import React from 'react'

const Person1 = () => {
  return (
    <div>
     <h3 style={{fontSize:"30px"}}>Big</h3>
    </div>
  )
}

export default Person1;


3) Module Style fo Componant 
- css only for that componat 
- just change name of css file "person.css" to "person.module.css"
- change import text to "import PersonStyle from "./person.module.css";"
- <p className={PersonStyle.para}>This is para</p>
